<TITLE> Hungary to open labour market to Romanian workers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BUCHAREST, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Hungary will fully open its labour market to qualified Romanian workers from January 2008, Prime Minister Ferenc Gyurcsany said on Wednesday after a joint cabinet meeting in Sibiu, central Romania. Romanian workers are at present granted automatic employment rights in Hungary in a limited number of professions. Hungary is struggling with labour shortages in some areas and is an attractive destination for ethnic Hungarians living in Romania. "I salute the decision, but that does not mean I want many Romanians to go to work abroad," Romanian Prime Minister Calin Tariceanu told a news conference. "I would rather we kept them here." Tariceanu said Romania is facing a growing labour shortage. Some 2 million Romanians -- more than one in 10 of the population -- have left the country since the fall of communism in 1989 to seek higher wages abro
